311
00:17:35.137 --> 00:17:37.637
and carried him up to this roof,

312
00:17:37.637 --> 00:17:41.637
and dropped him towards Mr. Komatsu who you had also lured out here.

313
00:17:43.237 --> 00:17:47.237
But consequently, you couldn't kill him like you wanted to.

314
00:17:48.637 --> 00:17:51.337
He'd never do a thing like that.

315
00:17:51.337 --> 00:17:53.537
And why would he want to...

316
00:17:53.537 --> 00:17:55.437
For what?

317
00:17:55.437 --> 00:17:59.437
What do I gain from killing Komatsu?

318
00:18:00.237 --> 00:18:03.137
You wanted Sakiko to suffer a great blow.

319
00:18:04.937 --> 00:18:06.537
He hit the bull's eye.

320
00:18:06.537 --> 00:18:08.537
Me?

321
00:18:08.537 --> 00:18:10.737
If his plan worked out,

322
00:18:10.737 --> 00:18:14.437
Mr. Fukurokoji as well as Mr. Komatsu wouldn't have made it.

323
00:18:18.237 --> 00:18:19.837
I'm sure if Sakiko saw that letter,

324
00:18:19.837 --> 00:18:22.937
she would've been shocked out of her wits.

325
00:18:22.937 --> 00:18:25.937
To think that he died an unfortunate death

326
00:18:25.937 --> 00:18:28.837
just because he was seduced by a woman.

327
00:18:28.837 --> 00:18:31.137
Excuse me! I know him!

328
00:18:31.137 --> 00:18:34.537
Why, Komat-chan?

329
00:18:34.537 --> 00:18:37.537
You're an idiot! Why?

330
00:18:39.937 --> 00:18:43.937
You were going to watch her and snicker.

331
00:18:44.037 --> 00:18:47.937
That in fact was your purpose, Mr. Yukigaya, right?

332
00:18:47.937 --> 00:18:51.937
That's why you had to have him bring the letter along no matter what.

333
00:18:52.437 --> 00:18:56.437
Because it was the most important thing to cause her grief.

334
00:18:58.137 --> 00:18:59.437
No.

335
00:18:59.437 --> 00:19:03.437
If I die holding a love letter that I received from a woman,

336
00:19:04.537 --> 00:19:06.737
why would Sakiko...

337
00:19:06.737 --> 00:19:08.837
It's about time you realize.

338
00:19:11.437 --> 00:19:12.837
What?

339
00:19:17.637 --> 00:19:20.637
Is it because I turned you down when you asked me for a date?

340
00:19:20.637 --> 00:19:22.337
Just because of something like that?

341
00:19:23.837 --> 00:19:26.737
I think he just couldn't forgive you for it.

342
00:19:26.737 --> 00:19:30.737
Especially because he's a confident person who knows no failure.

343
00:19:30.937 --> 00:19:33.237
But wait.

344
00:19:33.237 --> 00:19:36.437
Why did you want to kill Mr. Fukurokoji, too?

345
00:19:36.437 --> 00:19:38.737
There was no explanation for that.

346
00:19:38.737 --> 00:19:41.137
Anybody would've been okay, right?

347
00:19:41.137 --> 00:19:43.337
But, if you dropped a block or something,

348
00:19:43.337 --> 00:19:46.937
the police would've taken it to be premeditated murder.

349
00:19:46.937 --> 00:19:50.037
Therefore, you had to drop a human.

350
00:19:51.337 --> 00:19:54.737
Even the police wouldn't think that someone would use a human

351
00:19:54.737 --> 00:19:57.437
as a murder weapon.

352
00:19:57.437 --> 00:19:58.737
A murder weapon?

353
00:19:58.737 --> 00:20:02.737
Mr. Fukurokoji was dropped just to kill Mr. Komatsu.

354
00:20:04.037 --> 00:20:05.737
He was used as a human murder weapon.

355
00:20:05.737 --> 00:20:07.937
What?

356
00:20:07.937 --> 00:20:11.137
The person that you found to use

357
00:20:11.137 --> 00:20:14.337
just for that night was Mr. Fukurokoji, right?

358
00:20:14.337 --> 00:20:17.237
Since he used to always say he wanted to die,

359
00:20:17.237 --> 00:20:18.437
even if you dropped him from the roof,

360
00:20:18.437 --> 00:20:20.637
nobody would think it strange.

361
00:20:20.637 --> 00:20:23.237
They'd just think he finally committed suicide.

362
00:20:24.737 --> 00:20:28.737
Life has no meaning to trash like that anyway.

363
00:20:29.337 --> 00:20:33.337
Rather, it's unsightly for them to be living in this world.

364
00:20:33.537 --> 00:20:36.237
Yukigaya, you...

365
00:20:36.237 --> 00:20:39.937
Mr. Yukigaya, I would like to ask you something.

366
00:20:39.937 --> 00:20:41.537
It's over.

367
00:20:41.537 --> 00:20:44.637
